### Hadith 2:605

*Narrated Ibn Abbas:*

The Prophet (p.b.u.h) fixed Dhul-Hulaifa as the Miqat for the people of
Medina, Al-Juhfa for the people of Sham, Qarn-ul-Manazil for the people
of Najd, and Yalamlam for the people of Yemen; and these Mawaqit are for
those living at those very places, and besides them for those whom come
through them with the intention of performing Hajj and Umra; and whoever
is living within these Mawaqit should assume lhram from where he starts,
and the people of Mecca can assume Ihram from Mecca.

